21:26.626 --> 21:29.830
Hey Heritage, it is so awesome to be with you again today.

21:29.850 --> 21:31.693
I've got a question for you.

21:31.953 --> 21:33.135
It's very simple actually.

21:33.675 --> 21:37.561
When was the last time you felt incredibly refreshed?

21:38.242 --> 21:56.466
When was the last time your spirit and your soul and your body and your mind just felt rejuvenated, like incredibly rejuvenated, like you felt like all your tanks, your emotional tank, your spiritual tank, your relational tank, your physical tank were all

21:56.738 --> 22:16.960
full and you were ready to charge into life, you had plenty of reserves, you were ready to hit life with a veracity and a joy and a positivity that just kind of, I don't know, you were just ready to head out in life and do whatever you needed to do and take on whatever came at you.

22:18.462 --> 22:22.186
Chances are, it's probably been a while since you felt like that.

22:23.587 --> 22:26.130
And the reason why is because life throws

22:26.242 --> 22:29.126
so much at you, so much at me.

22:29.987 --> 22:32.630
There are so many things that come our way.

22:33.010 --> 22:38.477
So many things that just kind of take stuff out of our life.

22:38.617 --> 22:53.775
And if we take a few moments and examine why that is, if we actually are just a little bit critical or analytical, I don't mean critical or bad, I just mean if we analyze, why is it that so often I don't feel rejuvenated?

22:54.136 --> 22:55.858
I don't walk into my days

22:55.938 --> 22:57.540
with high expectations.

22:58.501 --> 23:05.711
Many times it's because we have said so many what I call mindless yeses.

23:06.813 --> 23:07.674
Mindless yeses.

23:07.754 --> 23:08.935
You know what a mindless yes is.

23:09.356 --> 23:12.400
That's when someone comes and says, hey, I'm moving next Thursday.

23:12.420 --> 23:13.321
Do you want to help me move?

23:13.762 --> 23:17.907
And the word yes comes out of our mouth before we ever able to think about it.

23:18.468 --> 23:22.834
When someone asks us to do them a favor and the word yes comes out of our mouth before we think about it.

23:23.490 --> 23:28.696
When our kids come home and they say, Mom, Dad, I want to be part of this traveling team, this sporting team.

23:28.756 --> 23:31.759
Can I please be part of it?

23:31.839 --> 23:32.841
Can I join the team?

23:32.921 --> 23:36.565
And we say yes before we think about it.

23:36.585 --> 23:41.550
Sometimes our mindless yeses come with a sense of even anticipation or excitement.

23:41.590 --> 23:45.114
For instance, we get a job offer, a promotion, perhaps.

23:45.975 --> 23:47.537
And it's going to mean a lot more travel.

23:47.777 --> 23:50.661
It's going to mean that we're going to be gone more from our families.

23:50.721 --> 23:51.922
But it's also going to mean

23:52.002 --> 23:52.583
more money.

23:52.643 --> 24:02.877
And so what begins to happen is we start justifying and say, well, you know, I'm going to be able to give a better quality of life to my family by saying yes.

24:02.937 --> 24:05.060
And so we don't really think about it critically.

24:05.080 --> 24:09.587
We don't really analyze whether or not that's actually the wisest thing to do.

24:09.627 --> 24:10.548
No, we don't do that.

24:10.648 --> 24:15.395
We just give a mindless yes.

24:15.415 --> 24:17.518
Chances are you've done that.

24:19.000 --> 24:20.402
Maybe you've bought something.

24:20.866 --> 24:33.219
You found yourself out around and you've been kind of looking for something and you find whatever it is that you've been looking for, but it's a little bit more money than you were prepared to spend or maybe it's actually not in the budget.

24:33.299 --> 24:39.025
And so, you know, you're there in that moment and you kind of do a mindless, yes, you just purchase it.

24:40.107 --> 24:44.371
And then you set yourself up for stress when you have to pay your bills.

24:46.033 --> 24:50.738
So often the thing that takes us away from refreshment and rejuvenation

24:51.938 --> 24:52.959
are mindless yeses.

24:54.140 --> 24:55.001
But here's what I know.

24:55.942 --> 24:58.505
What I know is that we don't have to live like that.

24:59.667 --> 25:16.385
Now, before you get mad at me, and perhaps you're saying, yes, Chris, I've said some mindless yeses before, before you get mad at me, could I say there's never going to be a message that I'm ever going to preach a heritage that I need to listen to more than this one?

25:16.866 --> 25:20.530
Because if I'm guilty of anything, I'm guilty of a lot of things, but if I'm guilty of anything,

25:20.706 --> 25:23.489
I continually say mindless yeses.

25:23.850 --> 25:26.633
I continually try and bite off more than I can chew.

25:26.653 --> 25:32.140
I continually try to do more than I think that more than anybody should be done.

25:32.220 --> 25:38.047
I think I can get more done than I really should be trying to get things done.

25:38.928 --> 25:42.872
In other words, I just run after way too many things at once.

25:42.912 --> 25:47.698
And what can happen over a period of time is that my soul gets to the point where it can be

25:49.570 --> 25:53.595
non refreshed, the opposite of rejuvenated.

25:53.615 --> 25:54.676
It can be tired.

25:55.277 --> 26:06.811
And if I'm not careful, I can end up with a soul that's kind of shriveled up, a spirit that starts becoming, I don't know, maybe cynical.

26:08.173 --> 26:15.922
Now, I have to tell you that that's not at all the way that God designed us to live, not at all, not at all.

26:16.962 --> 26:20.806
He wants us to live with purpose and meaning and fulfillment.

26:22.327 --> 26:26.291
And that's why this message is so incredibly important.

26:26.311 --> 26:30.755
Because God wants us to be aware of the mindless yeses that we say.

26:30.775 --> 26:40.885
And He wants to come alongside of us and help us to live so much more purposeful, so much more of a satisfying life.

26:40.905 --> 26:45.209
So as we continue with this message, I just wanted us to ask a couple of questions.

26:45.249 --> 26:45.970
And first is,

26:46.050 --> 26:50.355
Why do we say, yes, why do we say these mindless yeses?

26:50.735 --> 26:54.940
Well, first of all, I think it feels good in the moment.

26:54.960 --> 27:05.131
I think there are some times when some of us have a pent up desire to do everything and when someone comes and asks this, hey, do you want, even something recreational, like, do you want to go play golf or something?

27:05.211 --> 27:06.132
Maybe that's your thing.

27:06.172 --> 27:07.834
All of a sudden, yeah, let's go play golf.

27:07.854 --> 27:15.602
And then you realize, oh my goodness, that's, you know, if I'm playing 18 holes, which I do once a decade, if I say yes to that's a three hour commitment.

27:16.482 --> 27:19.025
Or we say, yes, I'll play on this softball team.

27:19.045 --> 27:24.211
And then we recognize, wow, that's going to take me away from my family X amount of hours every single week.

27:25.072 --> 27:29.036
But the reason we say yes is because it feels good in the moment.

27:29.116 --> 27:33.241
A friend asked us or someone asked us and it just feels good in the moment.

27:34.422 --> 27:44.914
And it's for people like us, because I can be in that camp as well, that the Holy Spirit wrote through a guy by the name of Solomon in the Old Testament of the Bible, these words.

27:45.538 --> 27:51.107
there is a path before each person that seems right, but it ends in death.

27:52.148 --> 27:57.277
It's like, it seems right in the moment, but man, if you're not there, well, you're gonna end up paying for it in the long run.

27:58.258 --> 28:02.745
So I think the first reason we say a mindless ass is because it feels good in the moment.

28:02.905 --> 28:07.353
I think the second reason is because we haven't really thought through our priorities.

28:08.214 --> 28:13.362
We haven't looked, again, at our schedules analytically, critically, in any way, shape, or form.

28:13.794 --> 28:34.505
We don't consider how saying yes to whatever it is that's coming our way is going to impact us spiritually, relationally with our family, how it's going to impact us financially, how it's going to impact us as far as our emotional health and our ability to really give ourselves to the things that we really do need to be giving ourselves to.

28:35.546 --> 28:40.754
So we haven't really considered what does it mean to live an intentional life.

28:42.306 --> 28:46.733
I think the third reason why we say mindless yes is because we don't want to disappoint someone.

28:47.354 --> 28:48.756
That might be your number one reason.

28:49.277 --> 28:51.120
Ah, Chris, I just don't want to disappoint them.

28:51.741 --> 28:56.709
Maybe this person has done something nice for you in the past or maybe you've kind of said, you know what?

28:56.729 --> 28:58.571
I kind of want to do some more recreational things.

28:58.591 --> 29:00.254
So maybe this is what I'm supposed to do.

29:00.334 --> 29:02.898
And so we don't want to disappoint the person.

29:02.918 --> 29:04.361
We don't want to disappoint our children.

29:05.442 --> 29:10.450
We don't want to disappoint another family member, a friend, a boss, a co-worker, whoever.

29:11.138 --> 29:12.941
we say a mindless yes.

29:13.321 --> 29:22.054
You know, when our teenager asks us if they can be part of a traveling team and we say, well, you know, I really want to support them and their athletics.

29:22.134 --> 29:24.017
And so we give a mindless yes.

29:25.299 --> 29:30.406
And we don't really consider, well, how is that really going to impact my child long term?

29:30.446 --> 29:32.890
How is that going to impact actually their spiritual walk?

29:33.170 --> 29:35.053
Are they going to have to say no to coming to church?

29:35.093 --> 29:37.377
Are they going to have to say no to going to youth group?

29:37.397 --> 29:38.418
Are they going to have to say,

29:38.562 --> 29:41.927
Note the things that actually we want to see developed in their life.

29:42.087 --> 29:45.312
And yet we don't want to disappoint our teenage kids.

29:45.332 --> 29:47.515
So we say a mindless yes.

29:49.859 --> 29:59.313
And finally, I think a lot of times that ultimately the reason we give a mindless yes is because we haven't considered that God actually has a plan for our life.

29:59.333 --> 30:03.079
That he actually does have a plan for us.

30:03.099 --> 30:07.986
Jesus said, and a guy by the name of John recorded it, the thief's purpose

30:08.066 --> 30:10.870
is to steal and kill and destroy.

30:12.313 --> 30:19.144
My purpose is to give you life, a rich and satisfying life.

30:19.164 --> 30:20.786
You know, so many people miss out on that.

30:22.108 --> 30:26.195
And the reason they miss out on it is because they're not really tuned in to God's voice.

30:27.857 --> 30:33.266
A couple weeks ago here at Heritage, we talked about the fact that often times, you know,

30:33.986 --> 30:36.510
Our spouse doesn't pick up the phone when we call them.

30:36.550 --> 30:39.273
And if we're not careful, we can begin to get irked.

30:39.293 --> 30:41.216
And, you know, we laughed a little bit about that.

30:41.276 --> 30:42.318
Here's the thing.

30:43.800 --> 30:51.070
What I said in that message is that the phone calls I really don't want to miss are God's phone calls.

30:52.512 --> 31:02.706
When he's trying to whisper something into my spirit, but I'm going at such a pace, I'm doing life at such a speed that I, and so many noises around me

31:03.042 --> 31:14.478
And I'm coming up to the stoplight and I'm looking at TikTok or I'm looking at my email or I'm responding to her texts and I never actually slowed down to listen to what he wants to say to me.

31:16.160 --> 31:24.552
And because of that, I'm saying mindless yeses because I'm not in tune to what Holy Spirit wants to say to me.

31:25.473 --> 31:31.762
I've forgotten that he actually has an awesome plan for my life, that he actually has

31:31.906 --> 31:36.051
an awesome purpose that he wants to see fulfilled in and through me.

31:37.172 --> 31:47.824
And if we can tune in to what he's saying to us, ah, if we can tune into his phone calls, quote unquote, it will lead to so much more of a satisfying and fulfilling life for us.

31:49.065 --> 31:53.190
So that's why we say mindless yeses.

31:54.411 --> 31:57.875
Now I want to look at what does it mean to say a strategic no?

31:58.976 --> 32:00.818
What does it mean to say a strategic no?

32:01.026 --> 32:06.992
See, there are times in our lives when the wisest, healthiest, and best way that we can respond to things is to say no.

32:08.133 --> 32:08.693
Jesus did.

32:09.514 --> 32:18.223
Jesus gave us a couple of incredible examples in the New Testament through his life of times when he gave a strategic no.

32:18.783 --> 32:19.964
Let me give you an example of one.

32:21.205 --> 32:21.926
I just love this.

32:22.026 --> 32:23.247
It's an incredible story.

32:23.288 --> 32:26.811
Jesus has just left first century church, what they call a synagogue.

32:27.391 --> 32:30.034
And one of his disciples, a guy by the name of Peter,

32:30.274 --> 32:36.062
who had a brother by the name of Andrew, they lived close by and so they invited Jesus over to their house.

32:36.723 --> 32:37.525
And this is what happens.

32:37.805 --> 32:42.732
As soon as they left the synagogue, they went with James and John to the home of Simon, that's Peter and Andrew.

32:43.574 --> 32:48.401
Now Simon's mother-in-law was in bed with a fever and they immediately told Jesus about her.

32:49.402 --> 32:55.832
So he went to her, took her hand, helped her up and the fever left her and she began to wait on them.

32:56.472 --> 32:57.554
Immediately she was healed.

32:58.882 --> 33:02.166
That evening after sunset, word got out, right?

33:02.386 --> 33:05.509
The people brought to Jesus all the sick and the demon possessed.

33:05.809 --> 33:08.432
Word got out, hey, Jesus is here and he's healing people.

33:09.253 --> 33:10.975
And the whole town gathered at the door.

33:11.496 --> 33:13.898
And Jesus healed many who had various diseases.

33:14.459 --> 33:16.060
He also drove out many demons.

33:16.801 --> 33:19.684
But he would not let the demons speak because they knew who he was.

33:20.926 --> 33:21.726
Now here's the thing.

33:22.808 --> 33:28.754
After that night, Peter, Andrew, Jim, or James, Jim and John, Pete, Andy,

33:28.898 --> 33:33.222
Jim and John, they all assume that the next day, woo-hoo, this is gonna continue.

33:33.503 --> 33:38.187
Like, we started this healing crusade last night and tomorrow morning it's gonna continue.

33:38.207 --> 33:40.350
Like, this is so cool, this is so much fun.

33:42.191 --> 33:46.776
But actually, Jesus was taking the heavenly father's phone call.

33:48.398 --> 33:49.118
Let me tell you what I mean.

33:49.959 --> 33:52.161
Look at the very next verse.

33:52.181 --> 33:56.786
Very early in the morning, the next morning, while it was still dark, Jesus got up

33:57.058 --> 34:00.762
left the house and went off to a solitary place where he prayed.

34:02.144 --> 34:05.628
Simon, that's Pete, and his companions went to look for him.

34:06.188 --> 34:10.113
And when they found him, they exclaimed, hey Jesus, everyone's looking for you.

34:10.133 --> 34:11.014
Like come back to town.

34:11.034 --> 34:12.255
We've got to keep this healing thing up.

34:12.996 --> 34:15.078
And Jesus replied, actually guys, no.

34:16.179 --> 34:20.144
Let's go somewhere else to the nearby villages so that I can preach there also.

34:20.704 --> 34:22.066
That is why I have come.

34:23.778 --> 34:27.824
So he traveled throughout Galilee preaching in their synagogues and driving out demons.

34:29.206 --> 34:33.453
Now you have to understand the disciples, when Jesus said that, they were blown out of their minds.

34:33.493 --> 34:34.835
They said, wait, what?

34:35.596 --> 34:36.798
Wait, wait, Jesus, are you kidding me?

34:36.818 --> 34:38.420
Like we got something going on here.

34:38.440 --> 34:39.382
We got to keep this going.

34:41.365 --> 34:47.394
But Jesus wasn't interested in what the crowd around him wanted him to do.

34:48.475 --> 34:50.258
No, he wasn't interested in that at all.

34:51.778 --> 34:54.861
He was much more interested in living a purpose-filled life.

34:55.702 --> 35:03.751
And there are six key words in that passage that we just read together that just kind of sum up how he viewed life.

35:04.052 --> 35:07.996
And they come out of Mark chapter one, verse 38, we just read it.

35:08.016 --> 35:10.839
He said, that is why I have come.

35:11.580 --> 35:12.661
See, Jesus had a purpose.

35:13.562 --> 35:17.707
Jesus was living his life from a purpose-filled center.

35:19.008 --> 35:20.370
He knew what he was here to do.

35:21.122 --> 35:24.386
He knew what his mission was, and he was living out his mission.

35:24.767 --> 35:28.472
And because of that, he wasn't going to say a mindless yes.

35:29.814 --> 35:35.241
He wasn't going to say yes to something that his Heavenly Father wasn't saying yes to.

35:36.463 --> 35:37.244
He was in tune.

35:37.404 --> 35:41.349
And by the way, that is not reserved just for Jesus.

35:42.170 --> 35:48.799
The invitation is for you and I to stop, listen, and obey.

35:50.301 --> 35:50.962
To stop.

35:52.098 --> 36:00.190
before we give a response to listen to what the Holy Spirit is saying to us and to obey what He's saying to us.

36:00.911 --> 36:02.193
That's our invitation.

36:03.995 --> 36:11.787
Years ago, oh my goodness, 2021 years ago, a guy by the name of Pastor Rick Warren wrote a book called The Purpose Driven Life.

36:12.788 --> 36:14.430
Perhaps you read it all those years ago.

36:15.292 --> 36:19.698
If not, I'd encourage you to go to Amazon and order a copy and read it.

36:20.706 --> 36:35.645
If you did read it all those years ago, I encourage you to get it off the bookshelf, get all the dust off, go back and just kind of skim it again and remind yourself of what it means to live a purpose-driven or a purpose-centered life.

36:36.506 --> 36:38.228
Let me give you one more example from Jesus' life.

36:39.410 --> 36:41.953
He's just fed 5,000 people.

36:42.934 --> 36:45.197
Oh my goodness, like what an incredible miracle.

36:45.257 --> 36:46.038
And everybody knew it.

36:46.418 --> 36:49.362
Like they recognized that Jesus took a few loaves of bread,

36:49.442 --> 36:57.955
couple of fishes and he had multiplied them supernaturally, miraculously to feed 5,000 men plus their wives plus their kids.

36:58.275 --> 37:04.124
I don't know, 15, 16,000 people, whatever there was, a bunch of people got fed that day.

37:04.144 --> 37:07.369
And right after that happened, this is what the Bible says in John chapter six.

37:08.110 --> 37:14.920
When the people saw him do this miraculous sign, they exclaimed, surely he's the prophet that we've been expecting.

37:15.761 --> 37:19.026
And when Jesus saw that they were ready to force him to become their king,

37:19.650 --> 37:21.672
He slipped away into the hills by himself.

37:23.875 --> 37:28.740
See, he wasn't going to say a mindless yes because he had a mission.

37:29.661 --> 37:39.111
And he stated that mission so incredibly clearly in Luke chapter 19, verse 10, when he said, the Son of man has come to seek and save those who are lost.

37:40.293 --> 37:41.254
That was his mission.

37:41.794 --> 37:46.640
His mission was to help people come into a relationship with his Heavenly Father.

37:46.660 --> 37:48.722
He wasn't interested about becoming a king.

37:49.218 --> 37:53.223
He wasn't interested about doing other things that other people might think he should do.

37:53.263 --> 37:56.066
He was interested in only doing what the Father wanted him to do.

37:57.368 --> 38:13.628
And when we live an intentional life, when we live from a purpose-filled center, oh my goodness, incredible things can happen, God can do even supernatural things through our life.

38:15.550 --> 38:18.674
It's fun to watch people who have a great intentionality

38:19.554 --> 38:25.881
You know, like great sports figures, Michael Jordan, Jackie Robinson from years ago, Michael Phelps.

38:27.022 --> 38:30.686
It's fun to watch people that get intentional with their lives.

38:30.766 --> 38:32.508
And so they say no to things.

38:33.249 --> 38:39.636
When they're in the height of their athletic career, they say no to a lot of things because they have a purpose.

38:39.656 --> 38:48.786
They're going after a gold medal or they're going after an NBA championship or they're going after, you know, a World Series or a Super Bowl ring, whatever it might be.

38:49.442 --> 38:52.826
Those are fun times to watch, but can I tell you something?

38:52.846 --> 38:56.331
The truth is you have greatness in you.

38:57.852 --> 39:04.741
I believe that with all my heart and I'm not just trying to make you feel better, I mean that.

39:05.101 --> 39:06.243
You have greatness in you.

39:07.024 --> 39:07.604
How do I know that?

39:07.645 --> 39:10.568
Because you're made in the image of Almighty God.

39:11.309 --> 39:16.796
God made you in his image and he has a unique and awesome and wonderful plan for your life.

39:17.397 --> 39:18.578
Look at what a guy bought in him.

39:18.690 --> 39:19.892
by the name of David writes.

39:20.673 --> 39:23.557
This is what he says in the Old Testament, Psalm chapter 139.

39:25.099 --> 39:28.063
He's talking about himself and he recognizes what God has done.

39:28.083 --> 39:33.951
He says, you made all the delicate inner parts of my body and you knit me together in my mother's womb.

39:34.752 --> 39:37.556
Thank you for making me so wonderfully complex.

39:37.977 --> 39:39.859
Your workmanship is marvelous.

39:40.240 --> 39:41.482
How well I know it.

39:42.543 --> 39:43.865
Can't just think about that for a minute.

39:43.985 --> 39:45.707
It's interesting to read that or to listen to it.

39:46.649 --> 39:47.570
But get the picture here.

39:47.842 --> 39:54.392
It's almost as if this guy, Dave, is looking in the mirror and he says, wow, God, you've made something pretty cool here.

39:55.253 --> 39:58.578
And it's not that he's being egotistical or prideful or arrogant.

39:59.099 --> 40:01.042
I mean, we all get that, but no, that's not what he's being.

40:01.443 --> 40:14.002
What he's talking about is, wow, God, when I think that you actually took the time to put inside of me passion, put inside of me goals, put inside of me direction,

40:14.082 --> 40:19.210
put inside of me purpose, put inside of me the desire to see awesome things happen.

40:19.971 --> 40:21.573
Wow.

40:21.593 --> 40:22.294
Thank you, God.

40:22.955 --> 40:27.021
Thank you for loving me enough that you've put something exciting in me.

40:28.263 --> 40:31.448
See, God has an incredibly unique plan for your life.

40:31.668 --> 40:36.476
He's given you the ability to do something better than 10,000 or 100,000 other people can do.

40:36.776 --> 40:37.377
I mean that.

40:38.018 --> 40:43.506
There are certain things that you can do infinitely better than other people around you can do.

40:43.618 --> 40:48.605
The Holy Spirit, God himself, is just inviting you more and more into that.

40:49.546 --> 40:55.854
In order to experience that, we're gonna have to probably say no to other things so that we can experience all that God has for us.

40:56.735 --> 41:06.388
And there's this guy by the name of Paul in the New Testament of the Bible who talks about the specific kind of decisions that you have to make in order to experience all that God has for you.

41:06.408 --> 41:10.674
He writes about it in a book that he writes to some folks in a city called Philippi.

41:11.266 --> 41:12.127
And this is what he writes.

41:12.147 --> 41:19.617
He says, everything else is worthless when compared with the infinite value of knowing Christ Jesus, my Lord.

41:20.318 --> 41:28.448
For his sake, I have discarded everything else, counting it all as garbage so that I can gain Christ and become one with him.

41:28.828 --> 41:31.232
In other words, yeah, I understand there's a lot of other things in my life.

41:31.252 --> 41:33.094
There are a lot of other things I can give my life to.

41:33.314 --> 41:33.975
But you know what?

41:33.995 --> 41:34.696
It's all garbage.

41:34.716 --> 41:36.338
Like, well, I compare it to

41:36.578 --> 41:45.973
Being in a relationship with Jesus Christ and getting to know him better and being in tune with what he has for me and for my purpose that he has for my life, oh man, nothing else compares.

41:46.373 --> 41:48.537
I can say no to this, I can say no to that.

41:48.937 --> 41:55.147
I don't have to say mindless yeses because I'm in tune with what God wants to do in my life.

41:56.910 --> 42:04.562
See, as we mentioned a few minutes ago, all that mattered to Jesus, say he wanted to do what the Heavenly Father wanted him to do.

42:06.274 --> 42:08.557
This blows my mind in that.

42:09.017 --> 42:16.026
In Colossians chapter one in the New Testament of the Bible, it tells us that Jesus is the one who spoke and everything came into existence.

42:17.027 --> 42:17.508
It says that.

42:18.048 --> 42:19.570
He's the one that spoke creation into being.

42:19.610 --> 42:21.072
It was his words.

42:21.493 --> 42:25.678
As a matter of fact, in John chapter one, it says about Jesus that he is the word.

42:25.958 --> 42:27.099
He speaks the word.

42:27.700 --> 42:30.003
And in Colossians, again, chapter one, it says he spoke creation.

42:30.544 --> 42:35.730
So this one who has the power to speak into existence, all creation,

42:36.002 --> 42:37.524
Said this, I tell you the truth.

42:37.784 --> 42:39.066
John chapter five verse 19.

42:39.366 --> 42:40.087
I tell you the truth.

42:40.428 --> 42:42.330
The son can do nothing by himself.

42:42.771 --> 42:44.693
He does only what he sees the father doing.

42:45.074 --> 42:47.437
Whatever the father does, the son also does.

42:49.039 --> 42:52.443
See the most extraordinary lives that I've ever witnessed.

42:53.244 --> 42:57.009
The most refreshed and rejuvenated people that I have ever known.

42:57.890 --> 43:00.293
The most joy filled people I've ever met.

43:01.294 --> 43:04.338
Live with a sense of intentionality about them.

43:05.122 --> 43:08.606
It comes out of a dynamic relationship with Jesus Christ that they have.

43:09.567 --> 43:11.789
And they've spent time pursuing him.

43:12.830 --> 43:15.173
They've spent intentional time pursuing him.

43:15.673 --> 43:19.177
And out of that pursuit has come an extraordinary life.

43:20.519 --> 43:24.123
Two people immediately come to mind, although I could literally give you many, many, many more.

43:24.183 --> 43:30.930
Matter of fact, I will give you a few more in just a minute, but I've had the privilege of knowing a kind of an internationally known author by the name of Bob Goff.

43:31.970 --> 43:35.194
And there's another guy in my life who I've known since I was a kid.

43:35.214 --> 43:38.377
His name is John Maxwell, kind of well-known in the leadership circles.

43:39.178 --> 43:41.060
I've known John most of my life.

43:42.422 --> 43:48.849
And I just have to tell you, what's interesting about those two guys is that they just live with an intentionality about themselves.

43:49.569 --> 43:51.091
And they live rejuvenated.

43:51.311 --> 43:52.372
They live refreshed.

43:52.813 --> 43:55.496
They live with a sense of purpose and being.

43:55.856 --> 43:56.517
Oh my goodness.

43:57.118 --> 43:57.899
It's awesome.

44:00.201 --> 44:01.042
But sometimes,

44:01.890 --> 44:06.295
They've had to say intentional no's, and they've done it through the power of Holy Spirit.

44:07.156 --> 44:09.379
I'm going to give you one last little example out of the Bible of that.

44:10.481 --> 44:14.425
This guy by the name of Paul, another guy by the name of Silas, were traveling together.

44:14.465 --> 44:17.709
And the book of Acts tells us about their travels.

44:17.729 --> 44:18.350
This is what it says.

44:18.410 --> 44:27.221
Paul and Silas traveled through the area of Fergia and Galatia because the Holy Spirit had prevented them from preaching the word in the province of Asia at that time.

44:28.603 --> 44:31.186
In other words, they were listening to what the Holy Spirit was saying.

44:31.330 --> 44:34.314
And he was telling them, I want you to go here and not here.

44:34.334 --> 44:38.501
There'll be a time to go over here, but right now I want you to go here.

44:39.622 --> 44:41.245
And they were in tune with the Holy Spirit.

44:42.847 --> 44:50.699
It's not just about people that are known because they write books and stuff where I see this intentionality played out.

44:50.719 --> 44:51.299
Oh my goodness.

44:52.762 --> 44:55.566
My incredible wife, I married way over my head.

44:55.646 --> 44:58.450
My wife, Mary, gets up every morning

44:59.426 --> 45:01.288
And she spends time alone with Holy Spirit.

45:01.308 --> 45:03.410
She just spends time in God's Word.

45:04.051 --> 45:05.312
She spends time praying.

45:05.352 --> 45:07.695
She spends time worshiping.

45:07.755 --> 45:09.637
She just enjoys the presence of Jesus.

45:10.618 --> 45:19.347
And out of that comes such a fulfilling life and such a powerful representation of who Jesus is.

45:19.988 --> 45:21.849
She says no to other things.

45:22.610 --> 45:26.194
And she doesn't say mindless yeses and it fills her up.

45:27.106 --> 45:34.014
I would encourage you to Google the guy by the name of Scott Harrison, who started this great organization called Charity Water.

45:35.395 --> 45:38.779
Man, at Google, him watch a video so of Scott.

45:38.819 --> 45:39.119
Scott.

45:39.820 --> 45:42.443
Amazing guy happens to be a Christ follower.

45:43.244 --> 45:53.456
But Scott started this incredible ministry and this incredible just organization that's helping get water to the poorest of the poor around the world.

45:54.837 --> 45:55.698
But it came.

45:56.002 --> 45:57.243
out of intentionality.

45:57.383 --> 45:59.125
It came out of an awakening he had.

45:59.346 --> 46:04.051
He had a spiritual awakening where God got a hole in his heart and he let God get a hole in his heart.

46:04.331 --> 46:05.632
He was into drugs.

46:05.672 --> 46:06.673
He was into sex.

46:06.693 --> 46:07.795
He was into alcohol.

46:07.815 --> 46:09.436
He was into the whole nine yards.

46:09.456 --> 46:11.559
And God said, Scott, I've got something better for you.

46:13.000 --> 46:15.022
And Scott moved into that with intentionality.

46:15.323 --> 46:20.208
He left a life behind that was getting him nowhere.

46:20.969 --> 46:23.191
And he said, yes to all that God had for him.

46:23.331 --> 46:25.874
And now he's literally changing lives around the globe.

46:27.234 --> 46:29.736
Christine Kane, incredible woman of God.

46:30.377 --> 46:33.380
You can Google Christine Kane and look up A21.

46:34.601 --> 46:40.566
Christine is helping so many kids around the world escape from sex trafficking.

46:41.107 --> 46:43.549
It's amazing what the A21 campaign is doing.

46:44.610 --> 46:46.032
I have a friend by the name of Joe Reed.

46:46.792 --> 46:48.774
Joe has suffered from mental illness.

46:48.834 --> 46:54.239
And in the last few years, when so many people have suffered with mental illness, Joe has taken that.

46:54.940 --> 46:55.941
And he said, you know what?

46:55.961 --> 46:57.202
I want to do my best.

46:57.570 --> 47:02.356
to help other people understand that they don't have to succumb to mental illness.

47:03.198 --> 47:10.728
And they don't have to go down deep, dark wows of pain that lead them to thoughts of suicide and ending their life.

47:10.748 --> 47:11.949
They don't have to go down that road.

47:12.650 --> 47:16.395
And he wrote a wonderful book called Broken Like Me.

47:17.076 --> 47:18.518
And you can check it out on Amazon.

47:19.499 --> 47:23.324
For a while, it was the most popular book on mental illness issues.

47:23.344 --> 47:23.985
Joe's a friend.

47:24.906 --> 47:27.570
And it's just been so much fun to watch Joe take

47:27.938 --> 47:30.302
intentionality, say, Holy Spirit, how can you use me?

47:30.682 --> 47:32.445
How can you use the things that I've been through?

47:33.767 --> 47:36.091
I'm going to have to say no to some things.

47:36.111 --> 47:38.395
I'm going to have to not say mindless yeses.

47:39.236 --> 47:44.725
And I'm going to take the time to work my FedEx job, true story, to work my job at FedEx.

47:44.745 --> 47:47.349
But then at night, man, I'm going to give myself to this manuscript.

47:48.070 --> 47:51.355
And now it's come out and it's blessing other people around the country.

47:53.298 --> 47:55.602
What are the things that God has placed inside of you?

47:57.058 --> 48:00.863
What is the purpose that he wants to fill in and through you?

48:02.285 --> 48:05.309
So I want to encourage you to just do a few things.

48:05.509 --> 48:12.297
Number one, start by just taking five or 10 minutes and think about what Holy Spirit is inviting you into.

48:12.938 --> 48:19.847
What unique and wonderful and at other times very ordinary things does he want to accomplish through your life?

48:21.589 --> 48:25.234
I'm begging you to pursue the dream that Holy Spirit

48:26.114 --> 48:31.820
has given you in the past or is rising up in you even now.

48:31.961 --> 48:36.886
Maybe consider what you believe he wants you to be known for in the long run.

48:37.347 --> 48:44.334
What does he want you to be known for as a friend, as a spouse, as a coworker, as a neighbor, as a parent?

48:45.576 --> 48:47.938
Take five or 10 minutes and just think through those things.

48:48.759 --> 48:54.866
Number two, what strategic knows will you need to say in order to live into all that God has for you?

48:56.034 --> 48:58.818
There are all kinds of, you might have to say some family knows.

48:59.058 --> 49:04.706
In other words, as a family, we're gonna say no to this or that opportunity because we want something better for our family.

49:05.147 --> 49:06.949
And other people, by the way, they won't understand it.

49:07.590 --> 49:10.014
Other people who wanna join that league, they're not gonna understand it.

49:11.456 --> 49:15.802
But if you live life with intentionality in the long run, you'll be so glad you did.

49:16.663 --> 49:18.606
Sometimes we have to say couple knows.

49:18.626 --> 49:24.594
And what I mean by that is that we have to say no to other things so that we can have a date, so that we can enjoy

49:25.282 --> 49:25.883
our spouse.

49:27.604 --> 49:31.808
Third, maybe a strategic no is we have to set up a boundary.

49:33.450 --> 49:35.191
And these boundaries are going to be different for all of us.

49:35.992 --> 49:38.935
We're going to have to say no to some things that other people can say yes to.

49:39.856 --> 49:42.799
But it's a boundary that we set up and it's a healthy thing.

49:43.299 --> 49:45.481
And again, don't be surprised if other people don't get it.

49:45.922 --> 49:47.703
Don't be surprised if other people don't understand.

49:48.384 --> 49:54.930
Just like Jim and John, Pete and Andy didn't necessarily understand when Jesus said no.

49:56.002 --> 50:00.168
But Jesus understood that there was a bigger picture, and he was going after that bigger picture.

50:01.410 --> 50:06.396
So, thirdly, and I'm not trying to be mean or negative about this, but what no do you need to say first?

50:07.939 --> 50:10.322
What do you need to say no to first?

50:11.504 --> 50:14.067
You know, maybe you can just say intentionally, I'm gonna say no to this.

50:15.149 --> 50:17.832
And finally, what powerful yes do you need to make?

50:18.774 --> 50:20.676
What is a powerful yes that you need to make?

50:21.357 --> 50:24.722
Spending more time with Jesus, praying, spending time in his word,

50:24.834 --> 50:29.119
listening to his voice, maybe worshiping, time and creation.

50:30.261 --> 50:31.863
Maybe you need to begin to deploy the gifts.

50:31.883 --> 50:34.847
Maybe God's given you gifts and you've just never put them into practice.

50:34.867 --> 50:37.270
He's given you abilities to do great things and to bless other people.

50:37.450 --> 50:38.892
You've never actually activated those.

50:39.132 --> 50:40.674
What does it look like for you to activate them?

50:42.036 --> 50:47.062
Maybe you need to join some community of believers.

50:47.082 --> 50:49.545
You need to be part of a small group here at Heritage.

50:49.565 --> 50:53.490
We'd love for you to be part of that and actively get involved in community.

50:54.114 --> 51:02.366
Maybe your strategic guess is to begin to surround yourself with other Christ followers that can encourage you and spur you on to all that God has for you.

51:02.707 --> 51:08.796
Maybe you need a great group of friends around you that can encourage you to all that God has for you.

51:10.859 --> 51:21.114
And maybe, just maybe, maybe you can get involved in serving some other people that perhaps up to this point you had a desire to serve, but you'd never taken the time to do it.

51:23.318 --> 51:23.538
Okay.

51:24.226 --> 51:24.767
final thing.

51:25.868 --> 51:34.536
If you're not in relationship with Jesus Christ, then can I just tell you, God uniquely and wonderfully made you.

51:35.737 --> 51:36.538
You're not a mistake.

51:37.939 --> 51:38.840
You're not an accident.

51:39.861 --> 51:46.507
You're here on purpose because God wants to do amazing things in you and through you.

51:47.308 --> 51:54.034
But that comes out of a phenomenally awesome, fulfilling relationship with him.

51:55.074 --> 51:57.097
And he wants to be in that relationship with you.

51:58.559 --> 52:00.743
So please reach out to us.

52:02.305 --> 52:03.427
Please connect with us.

52:03.547 --> 52:04.629
Contact us here at Heritage.

52:04.929 --> 52:08.475
We want to help you start that relationship with Jesus Christ.

52:09.316 --> 52:10.017
We want to do that.

52:11.380 --> 52:12.061
Would you pray with me?

52:13.463 --> 52:20.594
So God, thank you so much that you love us enough, that you care for us enough, that

52:20.802 --> 52:22.505
You put purpose inside of us.

52:22.585 --> 52:24.688
You put intentionality inside of us.

52:24.708 --> 52:27.332
You put dreams inside of us.

52:27.352 --> 52:41.154
And when we're aligned with that purpose and those dreams and that intentionality, and when we're in a healthy and growing relationship with you, ah, we don't get burnt out.

52:42.236 --> 52:43.598
No, there's rejuvenation.

52:43.638 --> 52:45.901
There's a wonderful pace.

52:47.083 --> 52:48.946
There's actually refreshment that comes.

52:50.786 --> 53:14.571
Jesus, you invite us in to a rhythm, even as Pastor Jeremiah was talking about last week, to a rhythm with you that allows us to experience everything that you created us to be, but to live with an intentionality and a purpose that causes us to actually feel refreshed.

53:15.872 --> 53:17.874
I pray that for my friends.

53:19.458 --> 53:21.184
I pray that you would help us to live into that.

53:21.245 --> 53:26.986
And if we're not in a relationship with you, I pray that we would make the decision to move into that relationship today.

53:28.692 --> 53:31.282
Thank you so much for your love for us in Jesus' name.

01:03:54.818 --> 01:04:03.769
I'm so grateful for this invitation to be intentional about creating space for us to encounter and live in the invitations that Holy Spirit has for us.

01:04:04.370 --> 01:04:15.903
I know that as we choose to identify boundaries in our lives and identify even what grid we're using to chase after the things of God together, it will pay huge dividends.

01:04:15.923 --> 01:04:21.330
With that in mind, I want to invite you to participate in some of our group offerings that we have kicking off

01:04:21.410 --> 01:04:22.592
in just a couple of weeks.

01:04:22.852 --> 01:04:31.904
There's one in particular that's all about helping you discern and define your purpose and mission and values in your family context.

